The development of the Bulgarian real estate market is spectacular, the attention of all Europe is turned to this country of the Balkans little mentioned in the past.
What, or who bought on this EU market which is still the cheapest but which will quickly become expensive?
The Bulgarian division of Re/Max.
Currently, in the real estate, Bulgaria is undoubtedly the most pop-up destination in Eastern Europe with its ski apartments and cheap seaside houses.
In the mountains, the most popular regions are Bansko, Borovec, Pamprovo and Vitosa and, on the shore of the sea, Albena, the "Golden Sables", the "Sun Coast", the ancient Sozopol and Nessebar but they are increasingly numerous looking for a building in the Kavarna and Balcik region as well.
According to analysts of Re/Max Bulgaria, sooner or later, the central region of the country, namely Veliko Tarnovo, Gabrovo, Elena, Triavna, will also awaken the interest of investors and they are also increasing to buy in the very cheap corner of Ruse.
Sofia, the capital, offers attractive opportunities as well, the shops and office surfaces promise the highest amortisation rate.
