The festival is not marked in red everywhere.
In Hungary, the law exactly defines the holidays and, around the holidays, it has become common to reorganize the working days whose number will decrease next year.
The holidays are not uniform in the EU and the United States as well.
Hungarian legislation distinguishes national and state holidays and rest days.
The days of rest are often linked to religious holidays or important historical events.
In Hungary, we celebrate the New Year, the last day of the year that ends and the first day of the New Year are also days of rest, this last even more so that the awakeners can rest calmly.
In one year, we have a total of 11 holidays marked in red.
March 15 is a national holiday, commemorating the revolution of 1848, as well as October 23 is the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On 20 August, we celebrate the constitution of our state, on 1 May is the day of work and on 1 and 2 November, we remember the members of our family and our dead friends.
We also have two days on Easter, Pentecostal and Christmas.
The days of our state, national or religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, according to the calendar, it has become common to reorganize the working days in cases or there is only one working day left before or after the party marked in red.
