The Entrepreneurship and Innovation Programme, intended for SMEs and entrepreneurs, should serve to obtain financial resources to encourage innovation within the enterprise.
Companies should get financial resources for the introduction of new technologies, research in the industry, but also for the introduction of new and more efficient management methods.
Until now, the Czech Republic was one of the least successful EU funding beneficiaries among the new members.
